ebola has been reported in multiple countries in west africa (see affected countries). cdc has issued a warning, level 3 travel notice for united states citizens to avoid all nonessential travel to guinea, liberia, and sierra leone. an alert, level 2 travel notice has also been issued for travelers to mali, where a cluster of cases has been reported. cdc advises travelers to mali to practice enhanced precautions and protect themselves by avoiding contact with the blood and body fluids of people who are sick because of the possibility they may be sick with ebola. an alert, level 2 travel notice is also in effect for the democratic republic of the congo (drc), where a small number of ebola cases have been reported that are not related to the ongoing ebola outbreak in west africa.
